GitHub Copilot: Ah yes, that makes perfect sense! üéØ

You want the emails to go directly to your **Gmail inbox** instead of staying in the cPanel webmail that you don't check.

There are a couple of ways to handle this:

## **Option 1: Email Forwarding (Recommended)**
Set up **automatic forwarding** in your cPanel so all emails to `stuart@1976uk.com` automatically forward to your Gmail inbox.

**How to do this:**
1. **Login to your HostGator cPanel**
2. **Find "Email" section ‚Üí "Forwarders"**
3. **Create a forwarder:**
   - From: `stuart@1976uk.com`
   - To: `your-gmail-address@gmail.com`
4. **Save it**

This way, every email sent to `stuart@1976uk.com` will automatically appear in your Gmail inbox! ‚ú®

## **Option 2: Update the Code (Alternative)**
Or I can update the functions.php to send emails directly to your Gmail address instead of the cPanel email.

**Which would you prefer?**
- Option 1 (email forwarding) keeps everything professional with your domain email but delivers to Gmail
- Option 2 (code change) sends directly to Gmail but loses the professional domain email aspect

**Email forwarding (Option 1) is usually the best approach** because:
- Keeps your professional `stuart@1976uk.com` address
- All emails automatically appear in Gmail
- You can still reply from your domain email
- More professional for business

